snippet.textDisplay:
I thought it will be power hungry. I build myself a "LED Wall" at some point and it drew >800W per module.
(1x1m / 60x60 LEDs) (800W at 80% brightness (all white) was the maximun my powersupply could handle.)
(Also i never build more then one module. That project was getting too expensive.)
(Also i have a few videos of it in action on my channel in case somone is intrestet in seeing it.)
PS: I'm sure microLEDs can also "burn-in" (wear off with use). It's just much slower then OLED.
